To add gh to authenticate to github automatically 

start - https://docs.github.com/en/get-started/getting-started-with-git/caching-your-github-credentials-in-git
next - https://cli.github.com/manual/gh_auth_login
last - https://cli.github.com/manual/gh_auth_setup-git

Run:
brew install git (add brew to path via instructions on terminal window)
brew install gh

-gh auth login 
-select https
-select Y
-enter scope[PAT/token] e.g 'repo'$GH_token
 -follow prompts
  -run 'gh setup-git' to make github use gh as a creds manager.
